# Cast — POC environment
# Copy to .env.local: cp .env.example .env.local
# (.env.local is git-ignored by Next.js and is the recommended file for
# local secrets. .env also works if you prefer it.)

# Required — OpenAI API key (D9). Read by the OpenAI SDK.
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Optional — GenAI mode (D9). default | cheap. Default: default.
# default = dall-e-3, three native sizes, one call per ratio.
# cheap   = gpt-image-1, one call per missing product + Sharp center-crop.
# CAST_GENAI_MODE=default

# Optional — Client-side GenAI mode badge (D32). Mirrors CAST_GENAI_MODE at
# build time so S1 can render a read-only mode pill without a runtime API call.
# Set both to the same value; if you set CAST_GENAI_MODE you should also set
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CAST_GENAI_MODE so the badge stays in sync with the server.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CAST_GENAI_MODE=default

# D22 (DAILY_GENERATION_LIMIT) was removed in D32 — the daily cap, the cap state
# file, and /api/cap no longer exist. The reviewer runs Cast locally with their
# own OPENAI_API_KEY, so client-side spend gating is out of scope for the POC.

# Optional — Dropbox Saver app key (public client ID, not a secret).
# Enables the "Export to Dropbox" button on the output grid.
# Also requires a Cloudflare Tunnel so Dropbox servers can reach your files.
# See README § "V2 Upgrade Paths → Cloud Export — Dropbox" for full setup.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DROPBOX_APP_KEY=
